What you need to know:

Popularly known as Kings of the South, South C United has more than 100 boys and girls from ages 12 years to the senior team who train under the guidance of well-trained and qualified coaching staff.“The main aim for the formation of the team is to keep the youth busy and away from drug and substance abuse, nurture untapped talents by giving the youth a platform to showcase their talent and inculcating discipline and life skills to the youth,” said Mr Khalif.